%Steps%

At this point, you should have created a new UE4 **Project** (pictured below).

![](NewUE4Project.png)

It's always good practice to keep your project's content organized. The first thing you're going to learn is how to create a folder that will store your imported content.

[REGION:note]
Before you get started: Download Quick Start Assets from the following link.
* [Sample Assets](Engine/Content/QuickStart/1/2/QuickStartSampleAssets.zip "Quick Start Sample Assets Download Link")
[/REGION]

1.	Extract the downloaded assets to a location on your computer (pictured below).

	![](Engine\Content\QuickStart\2\ExtractedContent.png)

1.	From the **Content Browser** in the Editor, click the **Add New** button (pictured below).

	![](Engine\Content\QuickStart\2\AddNewButton.png)

1.	Select **New Folder** to create a new folder in **'/Game'** (pictured below).

	![](Engine\Content\QuickStart\2\NewFolderSelection.png)

1.	Name the folder **'QuickStartContent'** (pictured below).

	![](Engine\Content\QuickStart\2\QuickStartContentFolder.png)

1.	Double-click the **'QuickStartContent'** folder.

[REGION:tip]
*Naming conventions matter! Be consistent when naming folders and files.*
[/REGION]
